Subject: Use hungry glob for string-match in test/elpy-config-test.el
Forwarded: https://github.com/jorgenschaefer/elpy/pull/1318
From: Nicholas D Steeves <nsteeves@gmail.com>
Applied-Upstream: https://github.com/jorgenschaefer/elpy/commit/558aaf1589745079db60277b8848a8d928f76720
Date: Tue, 20 Mar 2018 16:22:55 -0400

This is needed to fix failure of the
elpy-insert--pip-button-value-create-should-do-user-install test when
building on Debian.

Thanks to Jorgen Schaefer for the tip
---
 test/elpy-config-test.el | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/test/elpy-config-test.el b/test/elpy-config-test.el
index 9951ef1..37dfcd1 100644
--- a/test/elpy-config-test.el
+++ b/test/elpy-config-test.el
@@ -21,4 +21,4 @@
                                          (elpy/wait-for-output "Only")
                                          (buffer-string))))
                            (should (equal python-check-command "/foo/bar/flake8"))
-                           (should (string-match "python -m pip install flake8" output))))))
+                           (should (string-match "python -m pip install.*flake8" output))))))
